ing, “A Bill for an Act to Amend the Investments and Securities Act of 2007, to Provide for a greater Transparency and Accountability in Finances of Securities and Exchange Commission”,  and “A Bill for an Act to Establish Cancer Registry to make Provision for Compilation of Statistics Record of the Incidence of Cancer, to Provide a basis for direction of Programmes for Research and for other Cancer Prevention”, sponsored by Hon. Uzoma Abonta(PDP/Abia) and Hon. Nicholas Ossai(Delta/PDP) respectively. Vanguard .  The House of Representatives yesterday asked President Goodluck Jonathan to recall Nigeria’s envoy to South Africa over xenophobic attacks on foreigners. April 17, 2015 In "News" Members of both chambers of the National Assembly are piqued at the xenophobic attacks against Nigerians living in South Africa and have threatened reprisals, if the attacks continued. March 1, 2017 In "Headlines" ABUJA—MOVED by the deportation of Nigerians by the South African government, senators Tuesday asked the Federal Government to shut down all South African companies and immediately close the nation’s embassy in that country. March 7, 2012 In "News"